The paper deals with the security and privacy aspects of the Bitcoin P2P network, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) and computer networks (cs.NI). The techniques used in the paper involve analyzing network traffic and identifying patterns, which also falls under the category of distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). The paper also proposes countermeasures to mitigate the attacks, which falls under the category of social and information networks (cs.SI) and cryptography and security (cs.CY).
